cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.DL, cs.SE, cs.ET 

The paper discusses collaborative development methods for creating open and accessible lessons, which could fall under several sub-categories. "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the social and ethical implications of open and accessible education. "cs.CE" (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of lessons for scientific and engineering fields. "cs.DL" (Digital Libraries) is another possible category as the paper discusses the sustainability of open educational resources. "cs.SE" (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses collaborative development methods. "cs.ET" (Emerging Technologies) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of open source software and new technologies for lesson development.
